pale - fence: a fence marking a boundary

The term beyond the pale has been used for the fence to keep the East European Jews out of Europe. And for the fence to keep the Irish out of Northern Ireland. 

My parents left Bialystok on the Russian - Polish border around 1900 to avoid being beaten to death by Russians.

My wife's family left parts of Ireland a bit earlier to avoid being beaten and starved by the British.